        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:23PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Center Post, or 7 miles
north of Summerville, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, Trion, La Fayette, Naomi, Center Post, Linwood, and
Suttles Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
